<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-05-11T04:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-05-11T04:00:00-05:00" n="530" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d530">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War 1939/10848:
                            Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Egypt</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Kirk</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Cairo</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-05-11T12:00:00+03:00">May 11,
                                    1941—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received May 12—2:16 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>462. My 422, May 6, 7 p.m. It has been learned from a confidential source
                            that General Cunningham<note n="58" xml:id="d530fn58">Gen. Sir Alan
                                Cunningham, Commander in Chief of the British troops in East
                                Africa.</note> has now been authorized by London to approach the
                            French authorities at Djibouti with a view to ascertaining what
                            concessions they would be prepared to make in respect of the use of
                            harbor, railway and other facilities at that <pb facs="0601" n="589" xml:id="pg_589"/> port. No information is as yet available regarding
                            the progress of such negotiations.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Kirk</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>